-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Synthetic metagenome referenced in the GroopM paper:
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------

This folder contains the synthetic metagenomes used in the validation of GroopM
Files here are either reads, contigs and metadata. Reads were created by Ben
Woodcroft. Reads are error-free modelled on Illumina paired end (500bp insert).
The assembly was carried out using Velvet.

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
    READS:
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
There are three synthetic data sets.
Each of the files contains reads in FASTA format with descriptors:

>Sample{W}_Otu{X}_{Y}_{Z}

where:

    W is the sample number; 1,2 or 3
    X is the otuID
    Y is the read identifier
    Z is the paired read identifier; 1 or 2

Unfortunately we can't host these files on github directly, however they are available from
our ftp site. Please note that we keep no logs of who access this site.

You can download the test files from the following URLs

ftp://archy.ace.uq.edu.au/GroopM_test_data/Sample_1.fa.gz
ftp://archy.ace.uq.edu.au/GroopM_test_data/Sample_2.fa.gz
ftp://archy.ace.uq.edu.au/GroopM_test_data/Sample_3.fa.gz

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
    CONTIGS:
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
There are two contigs files.

contigs_all.fa.gz - The output from Velvet
contigs_500.fa.gz - All contigs >= 500bp. <- Used in the binning

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
    METADATA:
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Files:

README - This FILE!
Sample_otu_descriptions.tar.gz - Taxonomy for the references used in
                                 the samples
abundances.csv.gz - Relative abundances and read counts for each OTU in
                    each sample
groopm.bins.csv.gz - bin assignments made using GroopM for the sequences
                     in contigs_500.fa

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
